    {
        "content": "<p>Thank you so much!! I really loved the idea of \"<em>turning quantitative information into qualitative</em>\" Yes, by <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>L</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">L</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">L</span></span></span></span>, I meant to say <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>M</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">M</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">M</span></span></span></span>, and wanted to keep the notation the same as in the blog article.  I see!! I have not yet thought about in the direction of decorated cospans. I will think about it. Yes, I was thinking of using some of these ideas for developing suitable composable frameworks for  biochemical signalling pathways .</p>",
        "id": 495330476,
        "sender_full_name": "Adittya Chaudhuri",
        "timestamp": 1737565345
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Nice!  This issue of needing decorated rather than structured cospans already showed up in the case of open dynamical systems, where the morphisms again involve addition.   That was discussed on page 30 of <a href=\"http://math.ucr.edu/home/baez/cospans.pdf\">Structured versus decorated cospans</a>.  We may have talked about that already....</p>",
        "id": 495346758,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1737569684
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thank you so much!! I see the point. Yes, we discussed this issue in the context of open Petri nets with rates <a class=\"message-link\" href=\"/#narrow/channel/229199-learning.3A-questions/topic/Necessity.20of.20decorated.20cospans.20in.20open.20Petri.20nets.20with.20rate/near/447018021\">#learning: questions &gt; Necessity of decorated cospans in open Petri nets with rate @ ðŸ’¬</a></p>",
